      "0.09999999999999998\n",

      "-5.551115123125783e-17\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(0.3-0.2)\n",
    "print(0.4-0.2)\n",
    "print(0.3-(0.1+0.1+0.1))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We see the effect of finite precision in the first and the third. For the second case, as the two numbers are a factor of two apart, the precision error will cancel, giving the exact result."

    "i=0\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We get to a stage where epsilon is smaller than the precision with which floats are stored, and so the loop terminates.  For *exact* numerical operations, this should never end."
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def series_approx_cos(x,n):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Approximate cosine(x) using Taylor series with n terms\"\"\"\n",
    "    approx_cos = 0.0\n",
    "    sign = 1.0 # We will multiply this by -1 for each step to find (-1)^i\n",
    "    factorial = 1.0 # We will multiply by (i+1)*(i+2) to find (2i)!\n",
    "    for i in range(n):\n",
    "        approx_cos += sign * x**(2*i) / factorial\n",
    "        sign *= -1\n",
    "        factorial *= (2*i+1)*(2*i+2)\n",
    "    return approx_cos"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},

      "With  2  terms, the error is  0.040302305868139765\n",
      "With  3  terms, the error is  -0.0013643607985268646\n",
      "With  4  terms, the error is  2.4528090362019306e-05\n",
      "With  5  terms, the error is  -2.734969395401521e-07\n",

      "With  9  terms, the error is  0.0\n",
      "With  10  terms, the error is  1.1102230246251565e-16\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "true_answer = np.cos(1.0)\n",
    "print(\"For x=1.0, np.cos gives \",true_answer)\n",
    "for i in range(1,11):\n",
    "    approx_answer = series_approx_cos(1.0,i)\n",
    "    print(\"With \",i,\" terms, the error is \",true_answer - approx_answer)"
   ]

    "## Approximating reality\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set up time \n",
    "total_time = 2*365*24*60*60 # s\n",
    "days = 730 # Subdivision\n",
    "time = np.linspace(0,total_time,days)\n",
    "# Orbits\n",
    "period_ES = 365*24*60*60 # s\n",
    "period_ME = 28*24*60*60 # s\n",
    "\n",
    "# Physical constants, approximated\n",
    "radius_ES = 1.5e11 # m\n",
    "radius_ME = 3.8e8  # m\n",
    "mass_S = 2e30      # kg\n",
    "mass_E = 6e24      # kg\n",
    "mass_M = 7e22      # kg\n",
    "G = 6.7e-11        # m^3 /kg s^2"
   ]

   "metadata": {},

    "## Finding roots of functions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def cubic_to_solve(x):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate f(x) = x^3 - 2x^2 - x + 2\"\"\"\n",
    "    return x * x * x - 2 * x * x - x + 2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x113c6eba8>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x = np.arange(-2,3,0.1)\n",
    "plt.plot(x,cubic_to_solve(x))\n",
    "plt.axhline(color='k',ls=':',lw='0.5')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Finished after  20  iterations with root at  -1.0000009536743164\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Simple implementation of bisection method\n",
    "a = -1.5\n",
    "b = -0.5\n",
    "fa = cubic_to_solve(a)\n",
    "fb = cubic_to_solve(b)\n",
    "tol = 1e-6\n",
    "n = 0\n",
    "while abs(b-a)>tol:\n",
    "    n += 1\n",
    "    c = (a+b)/2\n",
    "    fc = cubic_to_solve(c)\n",
    "    if fc*fa>0: # a and c are same sign\n",
    "        a = c\n",
    "        fa = fc\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        b = c\n",
    "        fb = fc\n",
    "print(\"Finished after \",n,\" iterations with root at \",c)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def secant_method(fun,a,b,tol):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Implementation of secant method for root finding.\n",
    "    Inputs: \n",
    "        fun is the function\n",
    "        a, b bracket the root\n",
    "        tol is the tolerance\n",
    "    Outputs: number of iterations and root\"\"\"\n",
    "    x0 = a\n",
    "    x1 = b\n",
    "    fx0 = fun(a)\n",
    "    fx1 = fun(b)\n",
    "    n = 0\n",
    "    while abs(x1 - x0) > tol:\n",
    "        n += 1\n",
    "        # Calculate next point\n",
    "        dx = x1 - x0\n",
    "        df = fx1 - fx0\n",
    "        xnext = x1 - fx1 * dx / df\n",
    "        # Update storage\n",
    "        x0 = x1\n",
    "        x1 = xnext\n",
    "        fx0 = fx1\n",
    "        fx1 = fun(x1)\n",
    "    return n,x1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "After  7  iterations, root is  -0.9999999999918192\n"
     ]

   "source": [
    "iters, root = secant_method(cubic_to_solve,-1.5,-0.5,1e-6)\n",
    "print(\"After \",iters,\" iterations, root is \",root)"
   ]

    "def function_2D(x,y):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Specified 2D function\"\"\"\n",
    "    return 1.5*x*x + 2*x*y + 3*y*y - x + 4*y"
